The Nanoheat Wireless Heated Mug was designed by Michigan-based Design HMI and Green Lama .
It can maintain the temperature of hot drinks at 71°C (160°F) for up to 45 minutes .
The microheater weighs a little over one pound (454g) and can be charged wirelessly or using a traditional USB cord .
If the campaign is successful, the mugs will start shipping in August .